</disciplines><abstract>&lt;p&gt;The problem under investigation in this study was to develop some understanding of what it means to be a &quot;successful&quot; adult learner and to identify some characteristics of success that are related to non-traditional or self-directed learning. Three sources of data were utilized in this study: the original learning projects data described by Allen Tough in 1971, the study of older adults&#39; learning projects in Nebraska by Hiemstra in 1975, and a 1978 study by Zanqari of learning projects carried out by professional adult educators in Nebraska. There were a combined 325 adults in this comparative study.&lt;/p&gt;</abstract>
